<statement>
<p>Solve this system of equations using substitution.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{8}{x}-{5}{y}={0}</m> </p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle-{7}{x}+{6}{y}={13}</m></p>
<p><input type="text" style="width:10.6ch" name="qn0" id="qn0" value="" autocomplete="off" aria-label="Question 1" class="text"/></p>

</statement>
<solution>
<p><ul><li><m>\displaystyle{\left({5},{8}\right)}</m></li></ul></p><p>We chose (for no special reason) to solve the first equation for <m>\displaystyle{x}</m>.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{8}{x}+-{5}{y}={0}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{8}{x}={0}-{\left(-{5}{y}\right)}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{x}=\frac{{{0}-{\left(-{5}{y}\right)}}}{{8}}</m></p>
<p>Then we can substitute this into the second equation.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-{7}{\left(\frac{{{0}-{\left(-{5}{y}\right)}}}{{8}}\right)}+{6}{y}={13}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-\frac{{7}}{{8}}\cdot{\left({0}\right)}--\frac{{7}}{{8}}{\left(-{5}\right)}{y}+{6}{y}={13}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-{0}-{\left(-{4.375}\right)}{y}+{6}{y}={13}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-{4.375}{y}+{\left({6}\right)}{y}={13}--{0}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-{4.375}{y}+{\left({6}\right)}{y}={13}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{\left(-{4.375}+{\left({6}\right)}\right)}{y}={13}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{1.625}{y}={13}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{y}=\frac{{13}}{{1.625}}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{y}={8}</m></p>
<p>Finally we can substitute this y value into the first equation to solve for x.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{8}{x}+-{5}{\left({8}\right)}={0}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{8}{x}+{\left(-{40}\right)}={0}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{8}{x}={0}-{\left(-{40}\right)}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{8}{x}={40}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{x}=\frac{{40}}{{8}}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{x}={5}</m></p>
<p>Thus the answer is <m>\displaystyle{\left({5},{8}\right)}</m>.</p>

</solution>
